message: cgi.escape character replacement uri.escape used url encode url sent vcloud director api method http github.com fog fog blob v1.29.0 lib fog vcloud_director request compute l96 uri.escape doe url encode character meaning vcloud director using version 5.5 update interprets space cause following query fail type task sortdesc startdate filter name objectname mygateway startdate 2015 09t11 54.373 ... vcloud director interprets date stamp 2015 09t11 54.373 note missing time timezone uri.escape deprecated ruby 1.9.2 looked using cgi.escape instead seems aimed encoding query parameter value rather whole url uri.escape see discussion ruby core mailing list http cgi bin vframe.rb ruby ruby core 29293 29179 31097 encountered problem url encoding parameter value double equal used separate sub parameter key value i.e name also url encoded vcloud director api reject looking rfcs url seems behaviour using inside parameter value valid http 2009 every web developer must know url encoding http tools.ietf.org html rfc3986 section 2.4 ... proper solution url encode sub parameter value individually require modify api method able find way around using uri.escape cgi.escape fix issue running replacement specific character
